ed? How can future architects be interested in the history of architecture in order to locate themselves and determine their own position? This volume discusses the history of architecture in the context of art history, and the relativity of writing histories of architecture is shown through four stories about the Who, What, How, and Why of architecture. This way, Andri Gerber can introduce an adequately structured theory of history - a »meta-history«, which creates knowledge that enables the architect to relate to history in his work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aArchitecturexHistoriography. 0aArchitecturexHistory. 0aArchitecturexMethodology. 4aArchitekturgeschichte. 4aArchitekturtheorie. 4aIdeologie. 4aKritik. 4aKunstgeschichte. 4aMetapher. 4aRaum. 4aUtopie. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aArchitectural Theory.  aArt History.  aCritique.  aHistory of Architecture.  aHistory of Science.  aIdeology.  aMetaphor.  aSpace.  aUtopia.1 aAlessi, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerres, Uli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeister, Urs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchurk, Holger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStaub, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts and Architecture 2014z9783110369595oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014z9783111025223oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttra